<h2>The Craft of Words</h2>
<p><a href="http://www.fivesimplesteps.com/products/the-craft-of-words" target="_blank">The Craft of Words - Macrocopy</a> by The Standardistas is the next up in my list, and although I wasn't sure it was fully applicable to any projects I have on at the moment, I turned out to be so wrong and this kind of guide can be relevant to anyone, in many industries!</p>
<p>The book tells how many designers aren't fully aware of the impact that the words can have on a design at the early stages and pushes us to think about it in all parts of the process, not overlooking the impact they can have.</p>
<p>Thinking about it - words are obviously the most important part of any finished product so this book tries to drill into you the importance of considering them when designing.</p>
<p>From what I gathered reading this, macrocopy covers the entire tone and voice of an overall brand an image of a company and how they come across to the customer. The book aims at helping us communicate and get our message across through our design, not as an afterthought.</p>

