<h2>Creating Symbol Fonts</h2>
<p><a href="http://www.fivesimplesteps.com/products/creating-symbol-fonts" target="_blank">Creating Symbol Fonts</a> by Brian Suda grabbed my attention as at the time I was doing a lot with symbol fonts at work.</p>

<p>We started using icon fonts a long time ago in place of sprited icons basically as soon as we saw one of our webapps on a retina display iPad! Although this is the case, we have only really used pre made icon sets so far such as <a href="http://fortawesome.github.io/Font-Awesome/" target="_blank">Font Awesome</a> and I've used services such as <a href="http://icomoon.io/" target="_blank">Icomoon</a> and <a href="http://fontello.com/" target="_blank">Fontello</a> for personal projects.</p>
<p>Creating Symbol Fonts is a great introduction into what symbol fonts are, why they are awesome and how to implement them, leading on to some interesting ideas about the best, most semantic way to get them into your site, which I really appreciated.</p>
<p>I'd recommend it for anyone who's heard of using symbol fonts but isn't quite sure how to use them or just needs convincing of the many ways in which they can improve your development and ultimately your sites!</p>
<p>I've yet to take the last couple of chapters on board fully by spending the time creating my own symbol font from scratch but I'm keeping this book close for when the opportunity arises - hopefully in a new project soon.</p>

