<h2>Psychology for Designers</h2>
<p><a href="http://www.fivesimplesteps.com/products/psychology-for-designers" target="_blank">Psychology for Designers</a> by Joe Leech was my favourite of the books so far as right from the start I was drawn in with some of the ideas that I now know that I've consistently overlooked and taken for granted whilst designing and developing.</p>
<p>A quick overview of some main psychological methodologies and some design techniques really persuaded me that I need to do some more thorough research and apply these during my work projects and the book also shows how you can undertake research of your own and find resources to support it when making design decisions.</p>
<p>Although I don't have the time at the moment to further study some of these techniques it did intrigue me and I intend on getting a couple of basic psychology books the next time I'm down the local library as I found the themes in this book so interesting!</p>

<h2>Anyway&hellip;</h2>
<p>All of these books are so handy and as I say I'll be keeping them close to refer back to for a while yet.</p>
<p>I hope this wasn't too in-depth and I kept the reviews short and snappy enough, as these guides were for me!</p>
<p>There will be more in the next few weeks as I get through the rest of the <a href="http://www.fivesimplesteps.com/" target="_blank">5 Simple Steps pocket guides</a>.</p>
